BCNF and Normalization

Boyce Codd Normal Form
    Every non-trivial FD on Left Hand Side is not SuperKey
    then R is not BCNF

    R is in BCNF if every non-trivial FD then LHS is a SuperKey

    Decompose
    1 get the closure of LHS = T1
    2. T2 = LHS + (R-T1);


    Find key


